text: Lac-Moncouche is an unorganized territory in the Canadian province of Quebec, located in the regional county municipality of Lac-Saint-Jean-Est. It had a population of 0 in the Canada 2011 Census and covers a land area of 264.90 km2, entirely within the Laurentides Wildlife Reserve. ==See also== * List of unorganized territories in Quebec ==References== Category:Unorganized territories in Saguenay–Lac-Saint-Jean
title: Lac-Moncouche, Quebec
